\section{Conclusion}

This paper demonstrates that SM mass hierarchies emerge directly from cumulative SSV binding energy across lattice-derived cage layers, using the single parameter $\text{SSV}_0$ calibrated from the electron. The agreement with experimental masses supports the geometric origin of particle properties. Future papers will extend this framework to detailed particle interactions, decay processes, and experimental predictions.

